"title": "5450: poverty, spiritual",
"media_type": "Text",
"index_reference": "5450",
"language": "eng",
"review_level": "None",
"content": "<p>The lack of spiritual riches and gifts is seen by Scripture as an especially distressing cause of poverty. Awareness of spiritual poverty leads to a turning towards God in order to receive the riches he graciously offers through the gospel.</p>\n<h2>The ungodly are spiritually poor</h2>\n<h3>They lack faith</h3>\n<p><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Matt13:58\">MAT 13:58</a> parallel <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Mark6:6\">MRK 6:6</a></p>\n<h3>They lack understanding</h3>\n<p><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Prov10:21\">PRO 10:21</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Isa5:13\">ISA 5:13</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Isa56:10-Isa56:11\">ISA 56:10–56:11</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Jer5:4\">JER 5:4</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Hos4:6\">HOS 4:6</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Tim6:5\">1TI 6:5</a></p>\n<h3>They lack God</h3>\n<p><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Eph2:12\">EPH 2:12</a></p>\n<h3>They lack eternal life</h3>\n<p><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Matt16:26\">MAT 16:26</a> parallel <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Luke9:25\">LUK 9:25</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Luke12:20-Luke12:21\">LUK 12:20–12:21</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Luke16:22-Luke16:23\">LUK 16:22–16:23</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Jas5:1-Jas5:6\">JAS 5:1–5:6</a></p>\n<h3>They lack knowledge of their spiritual poverty</h3>\n<p><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Rev3:17\">REV 3:17</a></p>\n<h2>Spiritual poverty may be a judgment</h2>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Amos8:11\">AMO 8:11</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ps51:11\">PSA 51:11</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ps74:9\">PSA 74:9</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Lam2:9\">LAM 2:9</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ezek7:26\">EZK 7:26</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Matt13:14-Matt13:15\">MAT 13:14–13:15</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Rev2:5\">REV 2:5</a></p>\n<h2>The godly are aware of their poverty</h2>\n<h3>David recognised that he was poor and needy</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ps40:17\">PSA 40:17</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ps34:6\">PSA 34:6</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ps35:10\">PSA 35:10</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ps70:5\">PSA 70:5</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ps86:1\">PSA 86:1</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ps109:22\">PSA 109:22</a></p>\n<h3>Others recognise their spiritual poverty</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Rom7:18\">ROM 7:18</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Job42:6\">JOB 42:6</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ps8:3-Ps8:4\">PSA 8:3–8:4</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Luke5:8\">LUK 5:8</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Luke7:6\">LUK 7:6</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Rom7:24\">ROM 7:24</a></p>\n<h2>Those who know that they are poor will be blessed by God</h2>\n<h3>God will satisfy the poor in spirit</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Matt5:3\">MAT 5:3</a></strong> parallel <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Luke6:20-Luke6:21\">LUK 6:20–6:21</a> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Matt5:6\">MAT 5:6</a></p>\n<h3>God will save the poor in spirit</h3>\n<p><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ps116:6\">PSA 116:6</a></p>\n<h3>God will accept the poor in spirit</h3>\n<p><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ps51:17\">PSA 51:17</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Isa66:2\">ISA 66:2</a></p>\n<h3>God will be close to the poor in spirit</h3>\n<p><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ps34:18\">PSA 34:18</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Isa57:15\">ISA 57:15</a></p>\n<h3>God will hear the prayers of the poor in spirit</h3>\n<p><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ps102:17\">PSA 102:17</a></p>\n<h3>God will give grace to the poor in spirit</h3>\n<p><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Jas4:6\">JAS 4:6</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Jas4:10\">JAS 4:10</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Pet5:5-1Pet5:6\">1PE 5:5–5:6</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Prov3:34\">PRO 3:34</a></p>\n<h3>God will meet the needs of the poor in spirit</h3>\n<p><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Isa61:1\">ISA 61:1</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Luke1:53\">LUK 1:53</a></p>\n<h2>Spiritual riches are better than material riches</h2>\n<h3>Poverty with righteousness is better</h3>\n<p><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ps37:16\">PSA 37:16</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Prov15:16-Prov15:17\">PRO 15:16–15:17</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Prov16:8\">PRO 16:8</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Prov19:1\">PRO 19:1</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Prov19:22\">PRO 19:22</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Prov28:6\">PRO 28:6</a></p>\n<h3>Poverty with wisdom is better</h3>\n<p><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Prov16:16\">PRO 16:16</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Prov19:1\">PRO 19:1</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Prov19:22\">PRO 19:22</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Prov28:6\">PRO 28:6</a></p>\n<h3>Poverty with humility is better</h3>\n<p><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Prov16:19\">PRO 16:19</a></p>\n<h3>Poverty with peace and quiet are better</h3>\n<p><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Prov17:1\">PRO 17:1</a></p>\n<h3>Spiritual riches exalt the poor</h3>\n<p><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Jas1:9\">JAS 1:9</a></p>\n<h3>Spiritual riches endure</h3>\n<p><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Heb10:34\">HEB 10:34</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Heb11:37-Heb11:40\">HEB 11:37–11:40</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Pet1:4\">1PE 1:4</a></p>\n<h3>Spiritual riches more than compensate for material poverty</h3>\n<p><a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Cor6:10\">2CO 6:10</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Jas2:5\">JAS 2:5</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Rev2:9\">REV 2:9</a></p>",
